item.title: SABRE (Southall and Brent Studies)
item.description: SABRE (Southall and Brent Studies) is a population based cohort study comparing cardiovascular disease and diabetes between White British people and first-generation migrants of South Asian or African Carribean heritage recruited from West London (Jones, et al. 2020). Data collections include: Baseline (1988-91), 20-year follow up (2008-13), and 25-30 year follow up (2014-18). The SABRE cohort profiles can be viewed in Jones et al. (2020) and Tillin et al. (2012).
